Useful Xcode shortcuts for beginners

⌘: Command (Windows)
⇧ : Shift
⌃ : Control
⌥ : Option (Alt)

1. Open quickly (⌘ + ⇧ + O)
2. Find current file (⌘ + ⇧ + J)
3. Quick rename (⌘ + ⌃ + E)
4. Editing multiple lines (⌥)
Press Option key and drag your cursor around.
5. Code folding/unfolding (⌘ + ⌥ + Left Arrow[/Right Arrow])
6. Toggle Navigator (⌘ + 0)
7. Toggle Inspector (⌘ + ⌃ + ⌥ + 0)
8. Toggle Debug console (⌘ + ⇧ + Y)
9. Toggle Mini map (⌘ + ⇧ + ⌃ + M)
10. Commenting (⌘ + ⌃ + /)
